##First-line letter: Many War "epidemic" medical staff eager to implement the rotation

Wechat, bingdianweekly

Features, China Youth Daily's in depth reporting brand. We believe that news has more than one day of life.

Two paramedics at the Red Cross Hospital in Wuhan, on March 4,2010. China Youth Daily, China Youth Daily reporter, Wang Jiaxing

About 1672 words

Estimated reading time: 5 minutes

Author | Zhongqingbao Zhongqingwang Jiaxing, reporter

Editor | Zhang Guo

So far, many hospitals in Wuhan have been designated hospitals for fever patients for more than 40 days. When the reporter visited these hospitals recently, he heard many medical staff suggest that priority should be given to the medical staff who have been fighting for a long time in order to save energy for "winning the war" . These personnel after a long period of high-intensity work, physical and mental health have been seriously overdrawn.

"We have been fighting under heavy load and fatigue, " said Li Xu, the leader of the second group of medical teams from Sichuan Province to Hubei Province. On January 28, he and his team arrived in Wuhan to support the Wuhan Red Cross Hospital. He told reporters, whether it is the Red Cross hospital staff, or the arrival of medical team members, are rarely rest. Only in the last week did some people get one or two days off a week.

Since the outbreak, Wuhan Red Cross Hospital has admitted a large number of patients, the recent period of hospital admissions remains high. Li estimates that there is a shortfall of hundreds of health care workers, even without taking into account shifts.

In addition, the overall age of patients admitted to the Wuhan Red Cross Hospital is on the high side. Many patients are unable to take care of themselves and have a heavy workload. Since the outbreak of the epidemic, the hospital's nursing and logistics staff has been reduced a lot, and some medical and nursing staff have to take on nursing, cleaning and other work, adding to the workload.

Wuhan Red Cross Hospital is not an isolated case. Reporters learned in the interview, fixed-point Support Wuhan Jinyintan hospital part of the field medical team has not been off. A doctor at Wuhan's Fifth Hospital told reporters that the hospital had not been able to arrange rotation, or even two days a week. Only last week, some colleagues who had been on sick leave returned to work, and some of the staff were allowed to rest for two days.

On February 10, the National Health Commission, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security of the People's Republic of China, and the Ministry of Finance issued several measures to improve the working conditions of front line medical personnel and earnestly care for the physical and mental health of medical personnel, scientific calculation of the workload of medical staff, reasonable allocation of medical staff, not only to meet the demand for medical services, but also to protect the rest time of medical staff. Zeng Yixin, deputy director of the National Health Commission, said that front-line medical staff work hard, limited rest conditions, psychological pressure, high risk of infection.

On March 5,126 new cases were confirmed in Wuhan throughout the day, and 20,115 cases have been confirmed so far.

Ding Xiangyang, Deputy secretary-general of the State Council and a member of the Central Steering Group, said on March 6 that more than 3,000 health care workers in Hubei have so far been infected with the new pneumonia, of which 40 percent were infected in hospitals and 60 percent in communities.

February 18th, the Hubei Provincial People's government "some measures to further care for and inspire the first-line medical personnel for the prevention and control of the new coronavirus epidemic" proposed: "In principle, the continuous working time of the first-line medical personnel working in the shelter hospital or the General Designated Hospital shall not be longer than one month; the continuous working time of the first-line medical personnel working in the critical care designated hospital may be appropriately shortened. "

A doctor in the respiratory department at Wuhan Central Hospital told reporters he had not been on rotation since January 18. The department has arranged for some people to take shifts, but some medical staff, including him, have not taken a break and do not know when they will. He understood the situation, "we are responsible for the patient did not reduce, always can not ignore the patient. Each section has been on, the section chief also all the top line did not rest. "

Another Wuhan first-line medical staff said that his department has not been rotated off. After a month of continuous work, he applied to the head of the department for a rotation because he was unwell, but was told that the application for a rest should go through the leave procedure. This week, he and several of his colleagues finally took a few days off -- some of the time they had lost since January 20th.

Li Xu believes that in order to achieve the rotation of medical staff, we need to pool medical resources and integrate all medical teams. He told reporters that in view of the shortage of manpower and the need for rotation of medical and nursing personnel, he submitted a request for support to the National Health Commission on March 1, which has been co-ordinated by relevant departments. He understands that medical resources are scarce everywhere. At present, Sichuan has sent 10 batches of medical teams, 3 batches of disease control teams and 2 hospital-sense experts from the state, totaling 1,459 people.

The Under Secretary of the medical and Health Administration Bureau of the National Health Commission, Jiao Yahui, said earlier that the rotation and rest plan for overseas medical teams has been implemented. There are three modes of rotation, namely internal rotation, organizational rotation and regrouping. It has been reported that medical teams from Fujian, Shandong, Yunnan and Hebei provinces have been rotated off after more than months of work, while the Gansu Aid Hubei Medical Team has arranged for doctors to take 1.5-2 days off a day, nurses Work 1 day rest 2.5-3 days.
